headlines.description: — Joel Embiid went from fouling out to staying in.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 36, gets late call reversed in win over Cavs

headlines.description: — For the first time in nearly two months, the Miami Heat got an easy one.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat get rare easy win, roll past Grizzlies 138-119

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox hit a 3-pointer with 0.7 seconds left to give the Sacramento Kings a 117-114 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: De’Aaron Fox hits 3 at buzzer, Kings beat Bulls 117-114

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Kevin Porter Jr. scored 27 points and the Houston Rockets beat the short-handed Los Angeles Lakers 114-110 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter scores 27 points, Rockets beat short-handed Lakers

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 35 points and Jayson Tatum added 22 as the Boston Celtics held on to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 104-102 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 35, Celtics hold on to beat Wolves 104-102

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Christian Wood had 27 points and 13 rebounds and the Dallas Mavericks overcame a series of blunders at the end regulation to beat the San Antonio Spurs 137-128 in overtime Wednesday night without injured All-Stars Luka Doncic and Kyrie Irving.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wood has 27 points, 13 rebounds in Mavs' OT win over Spurs

events.name: Golden State Warriors at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Even in the midst of Stephen Curry putting on a shooting clinic during the third quarter, Kawhi Leonard and the Los Angeles Clippers didn't get rattled.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers beat Warriors 134-126 despite 50 points from Curry
